India’s Foreign Reserves Rise $266 million to $316.8 Billion

-- B y   V   R a m a k r i s h n a n
-- 
2011-09-23T11:30:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-23/india-s-foreign-reserves-rise-266-million-to-316-8-billion.html
India ’s foreign-exchange reserves
rose $266 million to $316.8 billion in the week ended Sept. 16,
the Mumbai-based Reserve Bank of India said in an e-mailed
statement today.  Foreign-currency assets advanced $202 million to $280.9
billion, while the nation’s gold reserves were unchanged at
$28.3 billion, the central bank said.  India’s special drawing rights with the International
Monetary Fund increased $2 million to $4.55 billion while its
reserves with the IMF rose $62 million to $2.99 billion.  Total reserves climbed by $29 billion in the past year, the
bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
V Ramakrishnan in Mumbai at 
